1
00:00:10,033 --> 00:00:11,300
<i> Hello, Edward!</i>

2
00:00:11,433 --> 00:00:13,533
<i>Look who still remembers
the address.</i>

3
00:00:13,667 --> 00:00:14,533
<i> You're starting something?</i>

4
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:16,033
<i> A web development company?</i>

5
00:00:16,167 --> 00:00:17,300
<i> If he wants to prove himself,</i>

6
00:00:17,433 --> 00:00:19,467
<i>he should do it without asking
for another check.</i>

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:20,667
<i> Forget it.</i>

8
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,233
<i>You shouldn't have offered help
in the first place.</i>

9
00:00:22,367 --> 00:00:24,600
<i>Edward, are you really sure
about Thea?</i>

10
00:00:24,733 --> 00:00:26,733
<i>She said you were the one who
spread her video scandal before.</i>

11
00:00:26,867 --> 00:00:28,200
<i>- Is that true?
- Yes.</i>

12
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:31,833
<i>If I could turn back time,
I wouldn't have done it.</i>

13
00:00:31,967 --> 00:00:33,300
<i> So Rodriguez really left?</i>

14
00:00:33,433 --> 00:00:36,233
<i>Love, they even took Velasco and
our Santos accounts with them.</i>

15
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,733
<i>I've got someone
who could help you.</i>

16
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:39,333
<i> And who exactly would that be?</i>

17
00:00:39,467 --> 00:00:40,667
<i> Hi, Paolo!</i>

18
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:41,867
<i> What is she doing here?</i>

19
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,300
<i>We'll be working together again.</i>

20
00:00:44,433 --> 00:00:45,633
<i> Mr. Orbos?</i>

21
00:00:45,767 --> 00:00:48,567
<i>Let me make you an offer.
Better property. Better terms.</i>

22
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:52,633
<i>I know something else that could
close the deal faster.</i>

23
00:00:52,767 --> 00:00:54,200
<i> Your choice.</i>

24
00:02:44,533 --> 00:02:45,900
<i> My child.</i>

25
00:02:51,633 --> 00:02:54,000
<i> Where's the money I gave you?</i>

26
00:02:54,900 --> 00:02:56,633
<i> All my savings.</i>

27
00:02:57,167 --> 00:02:58,500
<i> Everything I worked for.</i>

28
00:02:59,633 --> 00:03:00,600
<i> Dear...</i>

29
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,767
<i>I'm sorry. Something went wrong.</i>

30
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:04,867
<i> Sorry?</i>

31
00:03:06,100 --> 00:03:08,667
<i>You used my body
to pay your debts!</i>

32
00:03:09,300 --> 00:03:11,467
<i> You wasted all the money</i>

33
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,900
<i>that was supposed to be
for your medicine.</i>

34
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:16,133
<i>You chose gambling
over staying alive.</i>

35
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:19,300
<i> I had no other choice.</i>

36
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:20,833
<i> You had a choice, Dad!</i>

37
00:03:22,667 --> 00:03:24,000
<i>I'm the one
who had no choice!</i>

38
00:03:26,433 --> 00:03:29,033
<i>I'm always the one
who has to sacrifice.</i>

39
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:32,267
<i>I'm always the one who has
to get dirty just to save you!</i>

40
00:03:35,400 --> 00:03:38,167
<i>It's my duty to save you
because I'm your daughter.</i>

41
00:03:39,333 --> 00:03:41,167
<i>But that was the wrong kind
of obligation, Dad.</i>

42
00:03:43,067 --> 00:03:46,200
<i>I'm tired of getting dirty
just so you can live.</i>

43
00:03:47,733 --> 00:03:49,067
<i> My child...</i>

44
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:13,067
I promised myself...

45
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,267
I'd never use my body again...

46
00:04:19,067 --> 00:04:21,233
for money and ambition.

47
00:04:30,767 --> 00:04:33,400
But I couldn't rely on Edward.

48
00:04:37,700 --> 00:04:39,100
So this was the only way...

49
00:04:40,100 --> 00:04:42,600
to impress the Torrecampos.

50
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:48,067
To get into their world.

51
00:04:51,633 --> 00:04:54,733
<i> So, good news, everyone!</i>

52
00:04:54,867 --> 00:04:58,533
We've officially regained
the Orbos account.

53
00:04:59,100 --> 00:05:01,800
Signed, sealed,
and confirmed this morning.

54
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,733
Wow! That was fast, Thea!

55
00:05:05,867 --> 00:05:08,033
We thought it was impossible,
but you managed to pull it off.

56
00:05:08,167 --> 00:05:10,300
Seriously impressive.

57
00:05:10,433 --> 00:05:12,433
Hey, come on.

58
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:13,567
<i> That's incredible, Thea.</i>

59
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:15,867
We've been trying to win them
back for weeks.

60
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:17,767
How did you manage
to convince them?

61
00:05:19,367 --> 00:05:20,467
Well...

62
00:05:20,600 --> 00:05:22,433
just a lot of follow-ups, Paolo.

63
00:05:22,567 --> 00:05:27,867
Talk it out, read the room,
and maybe a little charm.

64
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,733
<i> Now, that's initiative.</i>

65
00:05:30,867 --> 00:05:33,067
Even Marj...

66
00:05:33,200 --> 00:05:34,933
couldn't get Orbos back.

67
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:38,633
<i> But you did.</i>

68
00:05:38,767 --> 00:05:39,667
Looks like we found ourselves

69
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,867
a new lucky charm
in this company.

70
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,400
Thank you.

71
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:48,800
<i> Oh, I don't know.</i>

72
00:05:48,933 --> 00:05:50,533
Maybe it was just luck.

73
00:05:50,667 --> 00:05:53,200
Or maybe they just preferred me
this time.

74
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:55,800
But Marj's still amazing.

75
00:05:55,933 --> 00:05:57,067
Right, Marj?

76
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,900
Congratulations, Thea.

77
00:05:59,033 --> 00:06:03,000
Well then, here's to new wins,
and to Thea Villarreal.

78
00:06:04,033 --> 00:06:06,233
Let's keep this momentum going.

79
00:06:20,167 --> 00:06:21,700
Thea's amazing, right?

80
00:06:22,300 --> 00:06:26,233
We chased Orbos for weeks
to no avail.

81
00:06:26,367 --> 00:06:29,000
She met him once,
and boom, deal done.

82
00:06:31,167 --> 00:06:32,767
Exactly.

83
00:06:32,900 --> 00:06:34,633
It's almost too good to be true.

84
00:06:35,567 --> 00:06:38,267
Well, whatever she did,
it worked.

85
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,733
Let's just hope she keeps it up.

86
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:44,133
At least the company's finally
making progress, right?

87
00:06:47,367 --> 00:06:50,000
Aren't you curious, Love,
how she did it?

88
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:53,667
We all know
Mr. Orbos is stubborn.

89
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:57,700
Why'd he change
his mind overnight?

90
00:06:59,633 --> 00:07:02,733
Maybe Thea's just that good.

91
00:07:04,567 --> 00:07:07,300
And can we not overthink it?

92
00:07:07,433 --> 00:07:08,200
Please?

93
00:07:08,333 --> 00:07:09,567
Work talk again.

94
00:07:10,300 --> 00:07:11,667
Office hours are over.

95
00:07:16,933 --> 00:07:18,800
Love, I'm exhausted.

96
00:07:18,933 --> 00:07:20,567
It's been a long day.

97
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:22,333
Exhausted?

98
00:07:22,767 --> 00:07:24,833
That's what you said last night.

99
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:27,233
But you still managed,
didn't you?

100
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:32,333
Yeah, we just did it last night.

101
00:07:33,433 --> 00:07:34,467
Then let's do it again.

102
00:07:35,467 --> 00:07:39,267
And dad's been waiting
for a grandkid, right?

103
00:07:41,233 --> 00:07:43,067
Come on.

104
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,033
Love, Love, Love.

105
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:48,233
Can we make the Torrecampo boy
next time?

106
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:49,867
Please?

107
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:51,967
Just one more.

108
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:53,500
Promise.

109
00:07:54,167 --> 00:07:55,733
Just one more.

110
00:07:59,767 --> 00:08:03,400
Chloe, what time's my meeting
with Mrs. Sanchez?

111
00:08:03,533 --> 00:08:05,667
- 10:00 AM, Ma'am.
- Okay.

112
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,967
And the Yakap Bata Foundation?

113
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,767
- 1:00 PM.
- Good morning.

114
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,333
- Good morning, Ma'am.
- Good morning.

115
00:08:12,267 --> 00:08:13,433
Marj.

116
00:08:17,567 --> 00:08:18,733
Thea.

117
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:21,567
Hi, Auntie!

118
00:08:21,733 --> 00:08:25,600
I just came by
to congratulate you personally.

119
00:08:26,633 --> 00:08:29,600
You got the Orbos account
so fast.

120
00:08:29,733 --> 00:08:31,567
Very impressive.

121
00:08:31,700 --> 00:08:33,533
Oh, thank you, Auntie.

122
00:08:33,667 --> 00:08:34,700
Maybe it was just luck

123
00:08:34,833 --> 00:08:37,733
that Mr. Orbos trusted
Torrecampo again.

124
00:08:38,767 --> 00:08:40,400
It's not just that, dear.

125
00:08:41,467 --> 00:08:43,333
You've got something special.

126
00:08:44,667 --> 00:08:45,600
Smart.

127
00:08:46,033 --> 00:08:47,300
Composed.

128
00:08:47,567 --> 00:08:48,533
Decisive.

129
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:51,667
Edward's lucky to have you.

130
00:08:51,800 --> 00:08:53,400
Thank you.

131
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,367
You know what?

132
00:08:54,500 --> 00:08:55,800
I really admire women

133
00:08:55,967 --> 00:08:58,567
who walk into a room
with charm and grace.

134
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:06,133
Not the kind who overreact
or bring drama.

135
00:09:07,900 --> 00:09:11,733
Oh, Auntie, Marj
was a great mentor to me before.

136
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:14,833
I learned a lot from her.

137
00:09:14,967 --> 00:09:16,300
Really?

138
00:09:17,833 --> 00:09:20,533
Then keep learning
from her mistakes.

139
00:09:26,033 --> 00:09:27,800
Excuse me. I have a meeting.

140
00:09:33,533 --> 00:09:37,067
Marj's actually doing
really well, too, Auntie.

141
00:09:37,200 --> 00:09:39,167
She's handling a lot right now.

142
00:09:40,067 --> 00:09:42,367
- Maybe she's just...
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

143
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:44,300
I'm sure she's doing her best.

144
00:09:45,733 --> 00:09:47,467
And so am I, Auntie.

145
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:50,800
I'll do my best to make
things easier around here.

146
00:09:50,933 --> 00:09:52,267
That's what I want to hear.

147
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:56,433
Maybe next time you can convince
Edward to come back.

148
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:01,200
Let's have lunch
at the house soon, okay?

149
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:02,200
Yes, of course.

150
00:10:02,333 --> 00:10:03,567
All right, I'll head out.

151
00:10:03,700 --> 00:10:04,900
Chloe.

152
00:10:38,133 --> 00:10:41,400
Marj, are you okay?
You look pale.

153
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:44,833
I'm not okay. But...

154
00:10:44,967 --> 00:10:46,067
I'll manage.

155
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:51,267
Marj, I just wanted to say,

156
00:10:51,400 --> 00:10:55,867
don't take whatever
Auntie Regina said seriously.

157
00:10:56,633 --> 00:10:57,967
You know how she is.

158
00:10:59,433 --> 00:11:02,167
She can be blunt.

159
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,000
She didn't mean
anything personal.

160
00:11:05,867 --> 00:11:07,833
You don't need to defend me.

161
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:11,100
I don't need a lawyer
against my mother-in-law.

162
00:11:12,467 --> 00:11:14,667
<i> That's not what I meant.</i>

163
00:11:14,800 --> 00:11:18,433
- I just wanted to say...
- I know that tone.

164
00:11:18,567 --> 00:11:20,467
"I'm just being a friend" tone?

165
00:11:20,600 --> 00:11:21,567
Enough, Thea.

166
00:11:22,133 --> 00:11:24,733
Can you stop pretending?

167
00:11:24,867 --> 00:11:26,700
Stop acting nice.

168
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:29,200
Marj.

169
00:11:30,067 --> 00:11:32,300
What do you want me to do?

170
00:11:32,433 --> 00:11:35,200
I've tried everything,
so you'll forgive me.

171
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:37,100
- What else do I need to do?
- Nothing.

172
00:11:37,233 --> 00:11:39,900
I don't want anything from you.

173
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:45,133
Marj.

174
00:11:45,933 --> 00:11:47,200
Wait.

175
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:48,833
What now?

176
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,667
Your dress.

177
00:11:53,067 --> 00:11:55,133
Marj, you're bleeding.

178
00:11:55,267 --> 00:11:56,967
We need to get you
to the hospital.

179
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:58,900
I'll take you.

180
00:12:08,600 --> 00:12:09,967
Doc, am I pregnant?

181
00:12:10,400 --> 00:12:11,800
Almost three months.

182
00:12:11,933 --> 00:12:13,667
Congratulations,
Mrs. Torrecampo.

183
00:12:15,467 --> 00:12:18,333
Congratulations,
Mom-to-be.

184
00:12:18,467 --> 00:12:20,933
So that's why I've been getting
tired and dizzy so easily.

185
00:12:21,467 --> 00:12:24,033
That explains
the mood swings, too.

186
00:12:24,767 --> 00:12:25,833
Oh my God.

187
00:12:27,333 --> 00:12:30,033
But, Doc,
I was bleeding earlier.

188
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:32,233
Is my baby okay?

189
00:12:32,367 --> 00:12:34,400
It's a good thing
you came in right away.

190
00:12:34,533 --> 00:12:36,200
If you'd waited any longer,

191
00:12:36,333 --> 00:12:38,067
there could've been
complications.

192
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:41,367
<i>But for now, the baby's stable.</i>

193
00:12:42,033 --> 00:12:43,933
I'll be back with the rest
of the test results.

194
00:12:44,067 --> 00:12:46,567
<i>Just get some rest
and avoid stress, okay?</i>

195
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:48,833
Okay, thank you, Doc.

196
00:12:48,967 --> 00:12:50,233
You're welcome.

197
00:12:50,367 --> 00:12:51,900
Paolo's on his way.

198
00:12:52,033 --> 00:12:53,300
He's almost here.

199
00:12:57,600 --> 00:13:01,500
If you hadn't come and kept
pushing me to forgive you,

200
00:13:02,267 --> 00:13:05,267
who knows what could've happened
to my baby and me.

201
00:13:07,867 --> 00:13:09,467
Good thing I'm persistent.

202
00:13:10,267 --> 00:13:11,900
Like how a sales agent
should be.

203
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:18,233
But, Marj,
what matters is you're safe.

204
00:13:18,833 --> 00:13:19,933
Both of you.

205
00:13:20,533 --> 00:13:24,567
I don't know if I'm ready
to forget what happened before,

206
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:25,633
but...

207
00:13:26,500 --> 00:13:27,767
thank you.

208
00:13:28,833 --> 00:13:31,000
I'm not asking you to forget.

209
00:13:34,067 --> 00:13:35,800
I just...

210
00:13:37,567 --> 00:13:39,767
I just want a chance
to make it right.

211
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:42,833
I don't know.

212
00:13:43,733 --> 00:13:44,700
But...

213
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,833
maybe someday.

214
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:52,900
That's all I need.

215
00:14:09,933 --> 00:14:14,100
<i>One day,
when you finally trust me again,</i>

216
00:14:14,233 --> 00:14:16,000
<i>it'll be easier for me to decide</i>

217
00:14:16,133 --> 00:14:20,933
<i>when and how to break you
in front of the Torrecampos.</i>

218
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,433
Is this it? Is this...

219
00:14:40,567 --> 00:14:41,667
What is this? The legs?

220
00:14:42,700 --> 00:14:43,800
Kind of.

221
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:46,900
I'm sure dad and mom
are going to love this.

222
00:14:51,067 --> 00:14:52,867
So after running some tests,

223
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:54,967
we saw that the baby's heartbeat
is strong.

224
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:58,133
However, the placenta
is implanted a bit low.

225
00:14:58,267 --> 00:14:59,533
<i> So we need to be careful.</i>

226
00:15:01,133 --> 00:15:02,667
Doc, what does that mean?

227
00:15:02,833 --> 00:15:07,133
It means there's a higher risk
of bleeding or miscarriage

228
00:15:07,267 --> 00:15:11,133
if you get too tired, stressed,
or overly active.

229
00:15:11,667 --> 00:15:13,800
You'll need complete bed rest.

230
00:15:14,367 --> 00:15:17,033
So avoid strenuous activities.

231
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:18,500
Heavy lifting.

232
00:15:18,633 --> 00:15:21,500
And even sexual activity, okay?

233
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:24,433
At least until
your next checkup.

234
00:15:24,567 --> 00:15:26,533
How serious is it, Doc?

235
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:30,267
As long as you follow my advice,
everything should be fine.

236
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:32,667
What's important
is that you avoid stress.

237
00:15:32,800 --> 00:15:35,500
And that you have someone at
home to help take care of you.

238
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:38,133
- I'll head out now.
- Okay.

239
00:15:38,267 --> 00:15:39,333
- Thank you, Doc.
- Okay.

240
00:15:40,433 --> 00:15:42,133
We can do this.

241
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:50,767
We've got this, okay?

242
00:15:59,400 --> 00:16:00,967
- Hi, Ma'am Marj.
- Hello.

243
00:16:01,100 --> 00:16:03,400
- Hi, Sir.
- Marj!

244
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:06,367
- Marj!
- There's my grandkid!

245
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:08,500
Hi, Paolo.

246
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:10,333
<i> Marj...</i>

247
00:16:12,767 --> 00:16:16,167
you know I've been waiting
a long time for this news.

248
00:16:17,733 --> 00:16:20,267
The first grandchild
of the Torrecampos.

249
00:16:21,100 --> 00:16:22,067
<i> What a blessing.</i>

250
00:16:22,533 --> 00:16:24,667
Thank you so much, Dad.

251
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:29,333
But the doctor said
my pregnancy's a bit delicate.

252
00:16:29,467 --> 00:16:31,433
So I really need to rest.

253
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:34,367
Of course, of course.
No overexerting yourself.

254
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:37,000
Tell us anything you need.

255
00:16:37,133 --> 00:16:39,300
You're carrying our legacy.

256
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,500
The future of our family.

257
00:16:41,667 --> 00:16:42,967
And family comes first.

258
00:16:44,267 --> 00:16:47,167
I'll take care of my sister.

259
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:50,767
If she gets tired,
I'll make sure she rests.

260
00:16:51,833 --> 00:16:54,033
I'll protect the baby.

261
00:16:54,167 --> 00:16:55,400
Promise, Uncle.

262
00:16:56,967 --> 00:17:00,167
Well, look at that.
The mom already has a bodyguard.

263
00:17:01,300 --> 00:17:02,600
Good job, young man.

264
00:17:03,967 --> 00:17:07,933
I hope the child gets
the best of both families.

265
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:09,600
Hopefully not too much of the...

266
00:17:09,733 --> 00:17:12,033
uniqueness of his special uncle.

267
00:17:13,033 --> 00:17:14,067
Mom...

268
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:18,500
the doctor said
Marj's pregnancy is sensitive.

269
00:17:18,633 --> 00:17:22,133
And she also said
to avoid stress.

270
00:17:22,267 --> 00:17:23,433
Okay?

271
00:17:23,567 --> 00:17:27,100
So maybe, temporarily,
let's call a ceasefire.

272
00:17:27,233 --> 00:17:28,600
For the baby.

273
00:17:29,433 --> 00:17:30,733
Yes. Yes, of course.

274
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:32,933
I mean, I don't want
to stress Marj out.

275
00:17:33,067 --> 00:17:36,200
Especially since she's not used
to our lifestyle yet.

276
00:17:37,533 --> 00:17:41,300
And I don't want to stress
the baby either. So yeah. Okay.

277
00:17:41,433 --> 00:17:43,400
Mom, for the baby.

278
00:17:44,900 --> 00:17:45,700
Okay.

279
00:17:46,267 --> 00:17:48,000
I'll keep the peace.

280
00:17:48,167 --> 00:17:49,967
I care about the child.

281
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:52,633
No matter who
the mother is.

282
00:17:53,667 --> 00:17:54,833
That's enough!

283
00:17:54,967 --> 00:17:56,033
All right?

284
00:17:56,900 --> 00:17:59,133
Let's not ruin
a beautiful day with drama.

285
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:02,367
Today, we celebrate.

286
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:04,767
The Torrecampo legacy lives on.

287
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:18,567
Well, look who finally decided
to come home.

288
00:18:19,367 --> 00:18:21,467
I thought you were
going to sleep at the bar.

289
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,867
By the way,
I've got good news for you.

290
00:18:26,167 --> 00:18:27,333
Marj is pregnant.

291
00:18:27,467 --> 00:18:30,933
And believe it or not,
we made up!

292
00:18:32,567 --> 00:18:33,767
You know,

293
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:35,433
I feel like she's going to ask
me to be the baby's godmother.

294
00:18:35,767 --> 00:18:36,500
Good for you.

295
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,733
What kind of reaction is that?

296
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:42,500
What now?
What happened this time?

297
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:44,333
Some investors pulled out
from my start-up.

298
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,533
I need to find new ones. ASAP.

299
00:18:49,633 --> 00:18:52,300
Well then, talk to your dad.

300
00:18:52,433 --> 00:18:55,767
Make peace already, so you can
go back to the family company.

301
00:18:55,933 --> 00:18:57,667
At least you'd be secure there.

302
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:58,733
For what?

303
00:18:58,867 --> 00:19:00,067
So I can beg him?

304
00:19:00,200 --> 00:19:01,833
<i>- No.
- So I can admit he was right?</i>

305
00:19:01,967 --> 00:19:02,900
No!

306
00:19:03,033 --> 00:19:05,867
So you can demand and reclaim
your position.

307
00:19:06,533 --> 00:19:08,267
Edward, you're good.

308
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,733
You know that.

309
00:19:11,467 --> 00:19:13,767
Oh, perfect timing.
I'm going to your house later.

310
00:19:14,267 --> 00:19:16,333
- Come with me.
- No.

311
00:19:16,467 --> 00:19:17,667
I'm not going back there.

312
00:19:17,800 --> 00:19:19,100
Do you want me to beg them?

313
00:19:20,633 --> 00:19:23,200
I'll figure this out. On my own.

314
00:19:25,700 --> 00:19:26,633
Okay.

315
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,100
Fine.

316
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:31,433
I won't ask your dad
for help anymore.

317
00:19:31,567 --> 00:19:34,400
But at least come with me
to your place, okay?

318
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:37,467
Marj invited me, too.
Just to show support.

319
00:19:37,600 --> 00:19:40,133
And maybe you want to see
your future niece or nephew?

320
00:19:45,833 --> 00:19:47,200
Edward...

321
00:19:48,033 --> 00:19:49,633
come on.

322
00:19:49,767 --> 00:19:51,100
It won't take long.

323
00:19:52,500 --> 00:19:56,267
Let them see
that their rebel son...

324
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:58,333
still cares about his family,

325
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:03,167
even if his bank account
is full of pride.

326
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:09,700
Come in!

327
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,333
- Hi, Marj.
- Hi, Thea.

328
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,600
How are you feeling?

329
00:20:19,567 --> 00:20:21,267
Oh, Edward's with you.

330
00:20:23,533 --> 00:20:24,433
Yeah, we just dropped by.

331
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:26,933
Thea wanted to see you.

332
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:32,667
Good thing you met Thea.

333
00:20:33,167 --> 00:20:36,167
I got the chance
to reconnect with her

334
00:20:36,333 --> 00:20:38,100
and even work with her again.

335
00:20:39,533 --> 00:20:43,933
I wanted to apologize
for judging her before.

336
00:20:46,533 --> 00:20:50,100
And thank you
for standing by her.

337
00:20:57,167 --> 00:20:59,733
So, let's get back
to the agenda.

338
00:20:59,867 --> 00:21:01,100
- Oh, yeah.
- What are you turning over?

339
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:04,533
Here it is. These are the...

340
00:21:04,667 --> 00:21:05,900
- Sorry.
- I'll help you.

341
00:21:06,033 --> 00:21:07,833
These are the accounts
I'm handling.

342
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:10,200
You'll take over for now.

343
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:12,100
I can't really monitor
them anymore.

344
00:21:12,233 --> 00:21:14,633
The doctor said
I need to rest.

345
00:21:15,467 --> 00:21:17,633
Oh, Marj,
don't worry about work.

346
00:21:17,767 --> 00:21:19,500
I'll handle everything.

347
00:21:20,633 --> 00:21:21,967
Thank you, Thea.

348
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:24,267
You know,
I'm worried about Paolo.

349
00:21:24,400 --> 00:21:27,167
He's dealing with so many
problems right now,

350
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:29,267
and I can't even help him.

351
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:31,633
Don't think about that.

352
00:21:31,767 --> 00:21:33,600
Don't think about that now.

353
00:21:33,733 --> 00:21:35,367
Focus on your baby.

354
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:38,667
I'll take care of Paolo.
I'll take care of everything.

355
00:21:39,733 --> 00:21:40,533
Right, Hon?

356
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:46,300
Maybe just focus on the tasks
Marj assigns you.

357
00:21:46,933 --> 00:21:48,700
Leave Paolo alone.
He's a grown man.

358
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:52,000
Exactly.

359
00:21:54,933 --> 00:21:56,500
Anyway, Marj,

360
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:58,767
I'll handle everything, okay?

361
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,433
You can trust me.

362
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,433
Hey, you've been showing up
at the mansion a lot lately.

363
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:16,367
I thought you were happy?

364
00:22:16,533 --> 00:22:18,200
Your boyfriend's right there
with you.

365
00:22:19,867 --> 00:22:21,067
I don't even know anymore.

366
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:24,133
You know,
working on Edward isn't easy.

367
00:22:24,267 --> 00:22:26,767
He's stubborn, full of pride,

368
00:22:26,900 --> 00:22:29,000
and he refuses
to make peace with his dad.

369
00:22:29,133 --> 00:22:31,533
And we both know he needs help.

370
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:34,967
Then why don't you just
go straight to the dad?

371
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:36,633
Sir Greg.

372
00:22:36,767 --> 00:22:38,500
You've got influence, right?

373
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:41,367
Of course!

374
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:44,500
Honestly, I'm even closer
to Greg than Edward is.

375
00:22:45,867 --> 00:22:49,400
But I don't really want
to get in between them.

376
00:22:50,233 --> 00:22:52,533
The rift between father
and son runs deep.

377
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:55,033
I knew it!

378
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,167
You picked the wrong
Torrecampo to date.

379
00:22:57,300 --> 00:22:59,300
You should've gone
for the older brother.

380
00:22:59,433 --> 00:23:00,700
Guaranteed win.

381
00:23:00,833 --> 00:23:02,833
Future CEO.

382
00:23:02,967 --> 00:23:05,500
But then Marj got pregnant.

383
00:23:05,633 --> 00:23:07,233
And if the first baby's a boy?

384
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:09,800
Huge points!

385
00:23:09,933 --> 00:23:12,133
He'll carry the family name.

386
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:14,233
What?

387
00:23:14,567 --> 00:23:16,467
Is it too late now?

388
00:23:16,600 --> 00:23:19,367
So what if he's married
and has kids?

389
00:23:20,633 --> 00:23:22,233
That's easy for me.

390
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:24,033
Piece of cake, girl.

391
00:23:26,167 --> 00:23:30,467
Girl, don't tell me you're
going to go after both brothers?

392
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:33,467
Hey! That's low, Lalaine!

393
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:34,767
Marj's my best friend.

394
00:23:34,900 --> 00:23:36,567
I'm not stealing anyone's man,
okay?

395
00:23:38,767 --> 00:23:40,033
That's disgusting!

396
00:23:42,633 --> 00:23:45,567
But if blessings come
knocking on my door...

397
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:48,233
then thank you, Lord.

398
00:23:48,367 --> 00:23:50,100
I won't say no.

399
00:23:53,133 --> 00:23:54,933
That was impressive,
Ms. Thea.

400
00:23:55,100 --> 00:23:57,300
<i>Everyone, thank you.
Meeting adjourned.</i>

401
00:24:10,433 --> 00:24:12,367
I didn't know you were
that sharp with numbers.

402
00:24:13,867 --> 00:24:15,533
I've had good mentors.

403
00:24:15,667 --> 00:24:17,767
And I've learned how to adapt.

404
00:24:17,900 --> 00:24:21,333
Especially when
I need to prove I belong.

405
00:24:21,467 --> 00:24:24,133
You don't need to prove
anything. You're doing great.

406
00:24:25,667 --> 00:24:26,967
Thanks, Boss.

407
00:24:28,467 --> 00:24:29,667
But hey,

408
00:24:30,500 --> 00:24:32,033
this is strictly work, okay?

409
00:24:32,667 --> 00:24:36,200
I don't want people thinking
I have special favors with you.

410
00:24:37,167 --> 00:24:38,533
Don't worry. No, no.

411
00:24:38,667 --> 00:24:40,100
I won't let this reach HR.

412
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:44,033
I'll go ahead.

413
00:25:14,167 --> 00:25:15,467
Yes?

414
00:25:19,933 --> 00:25:22,400
Love...

415
00:25:23,233 --> 00:25:24,533
you've been resting all day.

416
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:26,967
Maybe we could have
a little...

417
00:25:27,633 --> 00:25:29,233
cuddle time?

418
00:25:29,367 --> 00:25:31,633
The doctor said we can't yet.

419
00:25:31,767 --> 00:25:33,700
My pregnancy's delicate.

420
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,667
I'll be gentle.

421
00:25:36,867 --> 00:25:38,800
Come on, I just
really miss you.

422
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:40,567
I know, I know.

423
00:25:40,700 --> 00:25:43,900
But I don't want to risk
our baby.

424
00:25:44,533 --> 00:25:46,633
So please, just be patient
for a bit, okay?

425
00:25:55,133 --> 00:25:56,067
Love.

426
00:26:01,567 --> 00:26:02,967
Love.

427
00:26:04,533 --> 00:26:06,400
I just want our baby to be safe.

428
00:26:48,733 --> 00:26:51,167
I've been feeling
a little guilty lately.

429
00:26:51,300 --> 00:26:53,700
It's been a long time
since we did it, you know.

430
00:26:53,833 --> 00:26:56,933
I know all you care
about is the baby's safety.

431
00:26:57,067 --> 00:26:58,900
So that's why
you've been so irritable, son.

432
00:26:59,033 --> 00:27:01,533
If you can't have it at home,
look for it somewhere else.

433
00:27:01,667 --> 00:27:02,600
Simple as that.

434
00:27:02,733 --> 00:27:04,400
Are you coming home
for dinner tonight?

435
00:27:04,533 --> 00:27:06,333
I cooked all your favorites.

436
00:27:06,467 --> 00:27:07,467
I'll wait for you, okay?

437
00:27:07,600 --> 00:27:08,833
The country manager

438
00:27:08,967 --> 00:27:12,033
of NextConnect Global Services
messaged me.

439
00:27:12,167 --> 00:27:13,367
He's willing to meet tonight.

440
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:15,467
No matter how hard you try,

441
00:27:15,633 --> 00:27:17,667
if there's already a wall
between you and your husband,

442
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,400
it's not going to be easy
to tear it down.

443
00:27:19,533 --> 00:27:21,000
You decide.

444
00:27:21,433 --> 00:27:23,900
If you're coming, I'm game.
